{"body": "I think the api gets a bit cumbersome accepting 5 arguments, but I'm unsure about better ways now. An idea would be to accept a block, something like:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\npluralize(1, 'foo') { |count| content_tag(:span, count) }\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnother option is to create a separate method for that specific case. The method is so simple though, that I'm unsure about both approaches.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4561544", "created_at": "2012-03-18T14:32:38Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5490#issuecomment-4561544", "updated_at": "2012-03-18T14:32:38Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5490, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523ebd11bd354364b9012649"}, "id": 4561544, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5490"}
